Technical Analyst, Sr
02 May 2014 05:04 PM - UAE
. The Technical Analyst (TA), Senior works in a team environment with business analysts, system experts and development teams throughout the design, development and implementation phases of a project lifecycle. The TA, Senior will be assigned projects of diverse scope with minimal or no supervision. The TA, Senior defines system and application designs from functional business requirements. The TA, Senior is accountable for the performance, quality and effectiveness of project deliverables.Basic Requirements:Bachelor's Degree or at least 7 years of IT experienceAt least 5 years of IT experienceTravel up to 25%Qualified candidates, excluding current Navistar employees, must be legally authorized on an unrestricted basis (US Citizen, Legal Permanent Resident, Refugee or Asylee) to be employed in the United States. Navistar does not anticipate providing employment related work sponsorship for this position (e.g., H-1B status)Desired Skills:Positive attitude, ethics, and International Values which support our company''s values and a healthy, high performance cultureBachelors Degree in IT or Computer Science preferredTechnical knowledge of Windows operating systems, architecture, configuration and protocolExperience with application upgrades and troubleshooting application issuesExperience developing SQL and database objects, as well as performance tuning database queriesExperience defining complex logical and physical data modelsAble to implement messaging including one or more of the following concepts: message queues, SOA and web servicesExperience with web services creating XML documents and UML documentation - based on standards and transport protocolsExperience with Microsoft Office Products (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, MS Project)Knowledge of application globalization (sensitive to regional conventions, languages and alternate formats).Knowledge of project management and business analysis methodologiesExperience with development methodologies including working with an offshore model for development and supportStrong analytical and problem solving skillsSound judgment and reasoning skillsExcellent communication skills (oral and written) including strong presentation skillsAbility to translate functional designs into technical designs, and conversely to translate complex information into common termsAbility to both facilitate and actively participate in meetings with representatives from multiple business and/or IT unitsDemonstrates strong time management, organizational, & administrative skillsExperience with application testing with attention to quality and detailDemonstrated ability to develop and execute multi-person medium scale projectsUnderstands and utilizes Six Sigma methodology and applies the concepts within the project scopeDevelops a positive working relationships and a strong rapport with team members, and is able to influence decisions at the work group levelCompetencies:Ethics and Navistar ValuesPositive AttitudeBusiness AcumenCreativityFunctional/Technical SkillsDrive for ResultsContract ConversionVisit us at www.Navistar.com to discover more about our organization.We are an Equal Opportunity Employer.The Future Rides On UsDate: 2014-04-30Country: USState: ILCity: LislePostal Code: (more...)
